Here’s a TekAutomate Steps UI flow to save the setup to C:/setups/test.set and take a screenshot. This uses the recall step for setup save and save_screenshot for the screenshot.

```json
{
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "recall",
      "id": "save_setup",
      "params": {
        "recall_type": "setup",
        "recall_action": "save",
        "file_path": "C:/setups/test.set"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "save_screenshot",
      "id": "take_screenshot",
      "params": {
        "file_path": "C:/setups/test.png"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

- The setup is saved to C:/setups/test.set.
- The screenshot is saved to C:/setups/test.png (you can change the filename if needed).

